HEADWORD: Three-handed
<hw>Three"-hand`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Said of games
or contests where three persons play against each other, or two against
one; <as>as, a <ex>three-handed</ex> game of cards</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

